51","id":624143297,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDYyNDE0MzI5Nw==","user":{"login":"pakelley","id":7169800,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcxNjk4MDA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7169800?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/pakelley","html_url":"https://github.com/pakelley","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pakelley/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pakelley/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pakelley/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pakelley/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pakelley/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pakelley/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pakelley/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pakelley/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pakelley/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-05-05T16:00:46Z","updated_at":"2020-05-05T16:00:46Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"I definitely think having support for an ROC curve (or PR curve) would be useful! In addition to logging an array of metric values, it would be helpful to add support for a metric on the x-axis of the metric plot view. Some thought would need to go into the UX, of course, but I think this would be useful for visualizing the ROC curve.\r\n\r\nThe values @smurching proposed for `step`/`timestamp` are what I would personally expect as defaults, and I figure different values could be optionally passed in.\r\n\r\nAs far as use cases for an array of metric values, varying threshold values seems like the obvious one. Maybe this would also be useful for making predictions with multiple models for comparison? Maybe there's a more appropriate way of doing this though.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/comments/624143297/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"