pi.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/events/3526338538","actor":{"login":"AveshCSingh","id":1208791,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyMDg3OTE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1208791?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/AveshCSingh","html_url":"https://github.com/AveshCSingh","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AveshCSingh/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AveshCSingh/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AveshCSingh/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AveshCSingh/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AveshCSingh/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AveshCSingh/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AveshCSingh/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AveshCSingh/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/AveshCSingh/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"event":"labeled","commit_id":null,"commit_url":null,"created_at":"2020-07-08T17:44:37Z","label":{"name":"priority/important-longterm","color":"534cb5"},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/comments/901865691","html_url":"https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/issues/2451#issuecomment-901865691","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/2451","id":901865691,"node_id":"IC_kwDOCB5Jx841wWDb","user":{"login":"fulsi","id":17578413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3NTc4NDEz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/17578413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/fulsi","html_url":"https://github.com/fulsi","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fulsi/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fulsi/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fulsi/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fulsi/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fulsi/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fulsi/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fulsi/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fulsi/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fulsi/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-08-19T12:15:43Z","updated_at":"2021-08-19T12:15:43Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"Hello, \r\n\r\nIn the proposed workaround, if the number of fpr and tpr change between different trials I will not be possible to compare them properly (not aligned)\r\n\r\nI propose the following workaround. As the thresold, vary between 0 and 1, it will always be possible to compare different trial.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfpr, tpr, thresh = precision_recall_curve(y, scores, pos_label=2)\r\nlist_thresh = np.append(list_thresh, (1, ))  # view precision_recall_curve from sklearn metrics\r\nwith mlflow.start_run():\r\n    for idx in range(len(fpr)):\r\n        seuil = int(round(list_thresh[idx]*10000, 0))  # use high number to avoid several points on the same step\r\n        mlflow.log_metrics({'precision': precision[idx], 'rappel': recall[idx]}, step=seuil)\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nActually this workaround works for anything else, as long as the axis x keep the same interval through trials. The only constrainst is to put an integer instead of the step. It would be great to have an additionnal custom field (step / timestamp) to store whatever we want using float. \r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/comments/901865691/reactions","total_count":4,"+1":3,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"fulsi","id":17578413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3NTc4NDEz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/17578413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/fulsi","html_url":"https://g